{
  "legislative_session": "20252026",
  "identifier": "AB2562",
  "title": "Alcohol or other drug recovery and treatment programs and facilities: suicide prevention.",
  "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}",
  "classification": [
    "bill"
  ],
  "subject": [
    "Alcoholorotherdrugrecoveryandtreatmentprogramsandfacilities",
    "suicideprevention"
  ],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "summary",
      "abstract": "Existing law requires the State Department of Health Care Services to license and regulate adult alcohol or other drug recovery or treatment facilities that provide residential nonmedical services, as specified, and further requires the department to certify and regulate alcohol or other drug programs, as specified. Existing law requires a licensed facility to take specified actions, including to develop a plan to address when a resident relapses. Existing law requires a certified program to keep all policies and procedures in an operation manual.\n\nThis bill would require a licensed facility to develop a suicide prevention plan. The bill would authorize the department to implement the above-described requirement by bulletin or all-county or all-provider letter, after stakeholder input, until regulations are promulgated. The bill would require the department to promulgate regulations to implement the requirement no later than January 1, 2031. The bill would require a certified program to include in its operation manual a suicide prevention plan."
    }
  ],
